maintext:
Man who said he found girlfriend dead charged with murder
SNELLVILLE, Ga. (AP) — A Georgia man was charged with murder in his girlfriend’s death two days after he told police he found her dead in their backyard.
Police discovered Natasha Smith, 36, dead on Monday after her boyfriend, Antoine McFarlane, called to report her shooting, news outlets reported. He told police he found Smith shot dead when he got to the couple’s Snellville home.
Gwinnett police issued a warrant for his arrest after speaking to witnesses and collecting evidence at the scene. McFarlane, 35, was booked in county jail Wednesday.
